    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-06-01T09:31:26+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-01T09:31:26+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-01T00:01:26Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-01T00:01:26Z">
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A significant low pressure system moves over waters to the south of SA on Monday and Tuesday, reaching western Bass Strait Tuesday afternoon. Another low pressure system moves over waters to the south on Wednesday. A ridge of high pressure develops over western and northern parts as a series of troughs and fronts move over the south later in the week.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
